node.text:
The first full-quality full-length NFT music video, “Claire,” by @anyma_ofc & @marigoldff is out today on @superrare.co 🔥 This makes history! We utilized KSPEC, an open source museological grade protocol to expand the ERC-721 NFT standard. This groundbreaking technology allows for complex artworks, their provenance, indefinite transparent preservation, and unlimited file sizes on chain. 

This is a watershed moment that sets precedent as the worlds of digital art, crypto and music intersect. With few exceptions, NFTs have been limited to a fixed file size ranging from 30MB to a maximum 500MB, confining the length, fidelity, and creative scope of the work being sold. Meanwhile, music industry videos have been costly endeavors for artists, with sales of their music being the only option to recoup expenses. We are witnessing the emergence of a new opportunity for artists to engage with NFTs as a vehicle to deliver art and access directly to collectors. A new renaissance without gatekeepers and industry intermediaries is unfolding.

I am committed to immersing myself in the ever evolving NFT world and beyond thrilled to bring this one of its kind release to market. I predict all NFTs will embrace this protocol in due time. Thanks to @alessiodevecchi & @kanondotart for collaborating to bring this release to life!

node.text: Ayahuasca is driven by sound, by song, by whistling. Its ability to transform sound, including vocal sound, into the visual spectrum indicates that some kind of information processing membrane or boundary is being overcome by the pharmacology of this stuff. Things normally experienced as acoustic become visibly beheld, and it's quite spectacular.

node.text:
The Great Turn is a symbol of the potential for both transformation and disaster. How can each of us help create a better world? What is the moral pivot, the turning point upon which we will imagine and strive heroically to create that better world?

There are three primary compositional elements, the polarized body, the jewel web, and background tunnel of eyes, symbolizing three levels of our self. Reflecting on the meaning of the image, the Body feels the struggle of the ego caught in the web of the Mind, yet reaches toward the light of Spirit a tunnel of infinite awareness seeing everything. It is possible for us to locate our identity in any of those domains, yet the mystics would say only Spirit is real.
